CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper December 13, 1941, pg. 16, reads: "Here are the Harlem Globetrotters, famous professional quintet, ready for a busy season of play and traveling. Back row, left to right: Strong, Pressley, Price and Marcel. First row: Wilcox, Pittsburgh 'Y' star, who is getting a trial with the 'Trotter; Hudson, Ford and Jones."
TitMainTitle: Harlem Globetrotters basketball player, possibly Tony Wilcox, ready to shoot ball, in gym
